definitions.definition: A malleable , ductile , metallic element , resistant to corrosion , with atomic number 50 and symbol Sn.
An airtight container, made of tin or another metal, used to preserve food, or hold a liquid or some other product.
examples: a tin of baked beans; a tobacco tin ; a tin of shoe polish
Several tins of paint were needed to paint the house.
empty tins , cans, and plastic containers are recycled in the blue bins.
definitions.label_groups: New Zealand , Australia , South Africa , Ireland , British , countable

definitions.definition: A metal pan used for baking, roasting, storing food, etc.
The bottom part of the front wall , which is "out" if a player strikes it with the ball .

main_definition: ( uncountable ) A malleable , ductile , metallic element , resistant to corrosion , with atomic number 50 and symbol Sn.

( countable ) A metal pan used for baking, roasting, storing food, etc.
( countable , squash ) The bottom part of the front wall , which is "out" if a player strikes it with the ball .
( slang , dated , uncountable ) money , especially silver money.
